text.__SUMMARY__: Conus jorioi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.
text.Description: Predatory and venomous, these snails are capable of stinging humans. Their shell size attains 53 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail is found in the Atlantic Ocean off Northeastern Brazil.
